>>IN THE LAST TWO YEARS THERE
HAVE BEEN DRAMATIC SPIKES IN

00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:38.600
FOOD PRICES - EVEN SPARKING
RIOTS ON THREE CONTINENTS.

00:00:38.600 --> 00:00:42.330
THE FUTURE WARS MIGHT BE
FOUGHT AROUND FOOD AND WATER

00:00:42.330 --> 00:00:45.630
AS OPPOSED TO, SAY,
OIL AND TERRITORY.

00:00:45.630 --> 00:00:49.800
>>DIMINISHING NATURAL
RESOURCES AND RISING DEMAND

00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:52.800
FROM AN EXPLODING
WORLD POPULATION

00:00:52.800 --> 00:00:57.230
MEANS FOOD COULD BE IN
INCREASINGLY SHORT SUPPLY.

00:00:57.230 --> 00:01:00.370
THERE'S EVERY REASON TO
BE QUITE WORRIED ABOUT

00:01:00.370 --> 00:01:03.100
FOOD SECURITY
FOR THE WORLD.

00:01:03.100 --> 00:01:11.200


00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:14.570
>>IN TODAY'S GLOBAL ECONOMY
CONSUMERS IN RICH COUNTRIES

00:01:14.570 --> 00:01:16.770
HAVE GROWN USED TO A
LIMITLESS CHOICE OF FOOD

00:01:16.770 --> 00:01:18.700
FROM ACROSS
THE WORLD.

00:01:18.700 --> 00:01:23.300
LOCAL MARKETS HAVE BEEN
REPLACED BY GLOBAL ONES,

00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:26.200
AND FOOD HAS
BECOME A COMMODITY.

00:01:26.200 --> 00:01:36.270


00:01:36.270 --> 00:01:39.630
RIDLEY ROAD MARKET IN LONDON,
ENGLAND IS A PERFECT EXAMPLE

00:01:39.630 --> 00:01:42.430
OF OUR GLOBAL
FOOD CHAIN.

00:01:42.430 --> 00:01:45.730
THERE'S A HUGE RANGE HERE -
EVERYTHING UNDER THE SUN.

00:01:45.730 --> 00:01:49.070
AND NOT JUST THE BRITISH SUN
- THE MEDITERRANEAN SUN,

00:01:49.070 --> 00:01:51.570
THE AFRICAN SUN, THE
SOUTH AMERICAN SUN -

00:01:51.570 --> 00:01:53.470
PRODUCE FROM
ACROSS THE WORLD

00:01:53.470 --> 00:01:57.030
IS BEING SOLD ON THIS
LOCAL ENGLISH MARKET.

00:01:57.030 --> 00:02:02.170


00:02:02.170 --> 00:02:05.000
MIRRORING SHOPS AND
SUPERMARKETS ACROSS THE GLOBE,

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:07.400
THIS SCENE OF PLENTY,
ACCORDING TO EXPERTS

00:02:07.400 --> 00:02:10.430
LIKE TIM LANG,
CANNOT LAST.

00:02:10.430 --> 00:02:14.330
THE NIGHTMARE SCENARIO
IS THAT THERE WILL BE

00:02:14.330 --> 00:02:17.630
FOOD WARS, THERE WILL BE
SCARCITY WARS, THERE'LL BE

00:02:17.630 --> 00:02:21.770
RESOURCE WARS, FIGHTING FOR
MINERALS, FOR THE FERTILIZERS,

00:02:21.770 --> 00:02:25.630
THERE'S OIL RUNNING OUT,
THERE'S CLIMATE CHANGE COMING.

00:02:25.630 --> 00:02:28.870
I THINK THE
PARTY'S OVER.

00:02:28.870 --> 00:02:32.330
THE CAPACITY OF THE WORLD TO
PRODUCE AS MUCH ABUNDANTLY

00:02:32.330 --> 00:02:35.100
AS IT HAS DONE IS
BEGINNING TO BE SQUEEZED.

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:39.330
UNLESS WE CHANGE HOW WE
GROW FOOD, HOW WE EAT IT,

00:02:39.330 --> 00:02:42.770
WHAT WE EAT, HOW MUCH
WE'RE PREPARED TO PAY FOR IT,

00:02:42.770 --> 00:02:45.730
WE'RE WALKING
INTO CRISIS.

00:02:45.730 --> 00:02:54.230


00:02:54.230 --> 00:02:57.130
I VIEW THE CHALLENGE ON
THE FOOD FRONT AS PERHAPS

00:02:57.130 --> 00:03:01.530
THE LEADING CHALLENGE
FACING HUMANITY TODAY.

00:03:01.530 --> 00:03:05.000
>>LESTER BROWN IS THE FOUNDER
AND PRESIDENT OF THE INFLUENTIAL

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:08.170
CAMPAIGN GROUP, THE EARTH POLICY
INSTITUTE, AND HAS BEEN AN

00:03:08.170 --> 00:03:12.770
ENVIRONMENTAL AND AGRICULTURAL
ANALYST FOR 50 YEARS.

00:03:12.770 --> 00:03:15.400
DURING THE LAST HALF
OF THE LAST CENTURY

00:03:15.400 --> 00:03:17.330
THE NUMBER OF HUNGRY
PEOPLE IN THE WORLD

00:03:17.330 --> 00:03:20.470
WAS DECLINING, AND THEN
WHAT HAPPENED WAS THAT

00:03:20.470 --> 00:03:24.070
AFTER 2000 THE NUMBER OF
HUNGRY PEOPLE IN THE WORLD

00:03:24.070 --> 00:03:27.000
STOPPED DECLINING
AND BEGAN INCREASING

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:31.130
AND IN THE LAST TWO YEARS IT'S
GONE UP FAIRLY SUBSTANTIALLY.

00:03:31.130 --> 00:03:33.470
>>THE PREDICTIONS ARE
THAT A LOOMING FOOD CRISIS

00:03:33.470 --> 00:03:37.570
WILL AFFECT RICH AND
POOR COUNTRIES ALIKE.

00:03:37.570 --> 00:03:42.200
I THINK FOOD SECURITY, EVEN FOR
THOSE OF US LIVING IN AFFLUENT

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:44.900
COUNTRIES, IS GOING TO BECOME
AN ISSUE BECAUSE IT'S GOING TO

00:03:44.900 --> 00:03:51.970
TAKE MORE AND MORE OF OUR
INCOME TO FEED OURSELVES.

00:03:51.970 --> 00:03:55.100
IN THE U.S. WE'VE
BECOME ACCUSTOMED

00:03:55.100 --> 00:03:57.400
TO RATHER CHEAP
FOOD OVER THE YEARS

00:03:57.400 --> 00:04:00.400
AND THAT'S
BEGINNING TO CHANGE.

00:04:00.400 --> 00:04:03.400
WE'RE IN TROUBLE AND I
THINK MORE AND MORE PEOPLE

00:04:03.400 --> 00:04:05.800
SENSE THAT NOW.

00:04:05.800 --> 00:04:12.330


00:04:12.330 --> 00:04:14.100
>>BUT WHAT'S CHANGED?

00:04:14.100 --> 00:04:19.270
WHY ARE WE FACING
THIS LOOMING CRISIS?

00:04:19.270 --> 00:04:23.200
THE WORLD'S POPULATION HAS
DOUBLED OVER THE LAST 40 YEARS

00:04:23.200 --> 00:04:25.800
TO ALMOST
SEVEN BILLION.

00:04:25.800 --> 00:04:31.700


00:04:31.700 --> 00:04:34.870
AND JUST AT THE TIME WHEN THE
POPULATION IS SET TO SWELL BY

00:04:34.870 --> 00:04:37.870
A FURTHER TWO BILLION, QUESTIONS
HAVE BEEN RAISED ABOUT THE

00:04:37.870 --> 00:04:43.370
ABILITY OF MODERN AGRICULTURE
TO KEEP UP WITH DEMAND.

00:04:43.370 --> 00:04:47.070
IT IS ESTIMATED THAT IF WE CARRY
ON FARMING USING TODAY'S

00:04:47.070 --> 00:04:51.330
TECHNIQUES AND WITH YIELDS AT
TODAY'S LEVELS, THEN BY 2050

00:04:51.330 --> 00:04:56.530
WE WILL NEED TO DOUBLE THE
AMOUNT OF FOOD WE GROW.

00:04:56.530 --> 00:05:00.070
THIS INCREASE WOULD REQUIRE NEW
FARMING LAND THE SIZE OF BRAZIL

00:05:00.070 --> 00:05:03.800
TO PRODUCE ENOUGH
FOOD TO FEED THE WORLD.

00:05:03.800 --> 00:05:08.630
THE EXPECTATION IS THAT CROP
PRICES COULD BE, ON AVERAGE,

00:05:08.630 --> 00:05:14.770
SOME 40% HIGHER THAN THE
LONG TERM TRENDS TO DATE.

00:05:14.770 --> 00:05:18.270
>>RICHARD WARBURTON HAS
TO CONSIDER PREDICTIONS

00:05:18.270 --> 00:05:21.530
OF FUTURE FOOD PRICES
AS THE HEAD OF THE UK'S

00:05:21.530 --> 00:05:25.470
LARGEST AGRIBUSINESS
CONSULTANCY.

00:05:25.470 --> 00:05:30.670
THERE'S A FINITE AMOUNT OF LAND,
AND THAT FINITE AMOUNT OF USABLE

00:05:30.670 --> 00:05:34.130
ARABLE LAND WILL NOT SUPPORT
A DOUBLING IN FOOD PRODUCTION

00:05:34.130 --> 00:05:36.330
DUE IN 2050.

00:05:36.330 --> 00:05:40.600
I THINK POLICY MAKERS,
GOVERNMENT, ARE STARTING TO

00:05:40.600 --> 00:05:44.700
REALIZE THERE'S A CORRELATION
BETWEEN FOOD SECURITY

00:05:44.700 --> 00:05:47.800
AND POLITICAL
ECONOMIC STABILITY.

00:05:47.800 --> 00:05:51.100
I DON'T THINK IT'S TOO
FAR-FETCHED TO THINK THAT

00:05:51.100 --> 00:05:54.230
FUTURE WARS MIGHT BE FOUGHT
AROUND FOOD AND WATER

00:05:54.230 --> 00:05:57.630
AS OPPOSED TO, SAY,
OIL AND TERRITORY.

00:05:57.630 --> 00:06:04.600


00:06:04.600 --> 00:06:08.370
>>THIS ISN'T SOME
NIGHTMARE FUTURE SCENARIO.

00:06:08.370 --> 00:06:11.830
MANY EXPERTS SAY THAT WE HAVE
ALREADY SEEN THE EARLY TREMORS

00:06:11.830 --> 00:06:14.100
OF THE CRISIS TO COME.

00:06:14.100 --> 00:06:16.970
POOR GLOBAL HARVEST IN
2007 PUSHED AN EXTRA

00:06:16.970 --> 00:06:22.530
40 MILLION PEOPLE
INTO HUNGER.

00:06:22.530 --> 00:06:26.930
IN 2008 PEOPLE IN POORER
COUNTRIES ACROSS THE WORLD

00:06:26.930 --> 00:06:28.970
TOOK TO THE STREETS.

00:06:28.970 --> 00:06:31.270
THEY HAD A
COMMON CAUSE.

00:06:31.270 --> 00:06:34.870
FOOD PRICES WERE RISING SO
FAST THAT MILLIONS OF PEOPLE

00:06:34.870 --> 00:06:39.570
COULD NO LONGER AFFORD
THE FOOD IN THEIR SHOPS.

00:06:39.570 --> 00:06:43.700
THIS HAS BEEN SEEN BY
MANY AS A WARNING

00:06:43.700 --> 00:06:46.800
THAT FOOD SHORTAGES
IN YEARS TO COME

00:06:46.800 --> 00:06:51.570
WILL CAUSE MORE POLITICAL
AND ECONOMIC INSECURITY.

00:06:51.570 --> 00:06:55.070
SO WHAT ARE THE KEY FACTORS
PUSHING UP FOOD PRICES NOW

00:06:55.070 --> 00:06:57.830
AND IN THE FUTURE?

00:06:57.830 --> 00:07:00.400
MANY BELIEVE THAT ONE
OF THE BIGGEST FACTORS

00:07:00.400 --> 00:07:03.130
IS CLIMATE CHANGE.

00:07:03.130 --> 00:07:08.430


00:07:08.430 --> 00:07:12.800
DR. RAJENDRA PACHAURI ACCEPTED
THE NOBEL PEACE PRIZE

00:07:12.800 --> 00:07:15.000
ON BEHALF OF
HIS ORGANIZATION,

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:20.700
THE INTERGOVERNMENTAL PANEL
ON CLIMATE CHANGE, IN 2007.

00:07:20.700 --> 00:07:24.230
THERE'S A WHOLE RANGE OF
IMPACTS THAT ARE ASSOCIATED

00:07:24.230 --> 00:07:27.230
WITH CLIMATE CHANGE AND
THESE WILL HAVE DIFFERENT

00:07:27.230 --> 00:07:31.530
IMPACTS ON DIFFERENT
PARTS OF THE WORLD.

00:07:31.530 --> 00:07:36.700
IN THE CASE OF, SAY, THE UNITED
KINGDOM, EXTREME EVENTS

00:07:36.700 --> 00:07:41.830
INCLUDING DROUGHTS, FLOODS,
HUGE QUANTITIES OF RAINFALL

00:07:41.830 --> 00:07:45.200
IN A SHORT PERIOD OF TIME,
ARE CERTAINLY GOING TO

00:07:45.200 --> 00:07:51.400
HAVE A MAJOR IMPACT ON
THE PRODUCTION OF FOOD.

00:07:51.400 --> 00:07:54.600
IN THE CASE OF INDIA
WE'VE ESTIMATED THAT

00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:57.600
EVERY ONE DEGREE INCREASE IN
TEMPERATURE COULD LEAD TO

00:07:57.600 --> 00:08:01.970
5% TO 10%
REDUCTION IN YIELDS.

00:08:01.970 --> 00:08:08.000
AS EARLY AS 2020 SEVEN
COUNTRIES IN AFRICA ARE LIKELY

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:15.530
TO SUFFER A DECLINE IN YIELDS
OF SOME CROPS BY UP TO 50%.

00:08:15.530 --> 00:08:19.200
>>THE EFFECTS OF CLIMATE
CHANGE ON OUR FOOD SUPPLIES

00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:24.700
ARE PREDICTED TO BE FELT SOON
AND COULD BE FAR-REACHING.

00:08:24.700 --> 00:08:27.800
WORLDWIDE WE'RE NOT
GOING TO HAVE ENOUGH FOOD

00:08:27.800 --> 00:08:31.070
TO FEED ALL THE PEOPLE.

00:08:31.070 --> 00:08:36.030
THE FIRST THING THAT'LL HAPPEN
IS THAT PRICES WILL INCREASE.

00:08:36.030 --> 00:08:39.400
THERE WILL BE PERIODS WHEN
PERHAPS WHAT THEY WANT TO EAT

00:08:39.400 --> 00:08:41.870
MAY NOT EVEN
BE AVAILABLE.

00:08:41.870 --> 00:08:44.200
SO THERE'S EVERY REASON
TO BE QUITE WORRIED

00:08:44.200 --> 00:08:49.000
ABOUT FOOD SECURITY
FOR THE WORLD.

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:54.100
>>CLIMATE CHANGE FORECASTS
CAN SEEM LIKE DISCONNECTED

00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:58.000
PREDICTIONS OF DOOM
FOR A FARAWAY TIME.

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:01.900
BUT FOR SOME, CLIMATE
CHANGE IS ALREADY A REALITY,

00:09:01.900 --> 00:09:08.470
A STRUGGLE TO GET FROM
ONE DAY TO THE NEXT.

00:09:08.470 --> 00:09:12.630
DROUGHTS IN PARTS
OF KENYA HAVE BECOME

00:09:12.630 --> 00:09:18.070
FOUR TIMES MORE COMMON
IN THE LAST 25 YEARS.

00:09:18.070 --> 00:09:21.230
THE COUNTRY HAS JUST SUFFERED
ITS THIRD FAILED HARVEST

00:09:21.230 --> 00:09:25.230
IN A ROW AND THE WORST
DROUGHT IN MORE THAN A DECADE.

00:09:25.230 --> 00:09:29.200
SOME OF THE WORST HIT HAVE BEEN
THE MAASAI PEOPLE WHO HAVE

00:09:29.200 --> 00:09:33.600
HERDED LIVESTOCK IN THIS PART
OF THE WORLD FOR CENTURIES.

00:09:33.600 --> 00:09:50.200


00:09:50.200 --> 00:09:53.270
CHIEF SAMMY TARAKUAIE IS A
LEADER OF A MAASAI COMMUNITY

00:09:53.270 --> 00:09:56.330
OF ABOUT 9,000 PEOPLE
WHO LIVE SOME 75 MILES

00:09:56.330 --> 00:10:01.070
OUTSIDE NAIROBI
IN THE RIFT VALLEY.

00:10:01.070 --> 00:10:04.000
HE HAS SEEN THE CHANGE IN
THE LOCAL WEATHER PATTERNS

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:06.300
IN HIS LIFETIME.

00:10:06.300 --> 00:10:27.170


00:10:27.170 --> 00:10:30.570
>>BEFORE THE WEATHER BECAME
SO UNPREDICTABLE THIS WOULD

00:10:30.570 --> 00:10:34.600
HAVE BEEN THE BEST TIME OF
YEAR FOR A MAASAI HERDSMAN.

00:10:34.600 --> 00:10:48.700


00:10:48.700 --> 00:10:51.030
>>THE CHIEF HAS HAD A
DRAMATIC LOSS OF CATTLE

00:10:51.030 --> 00:10:53.700
IN THE LAST NINE
OR TEN YEARS.

