00:12:17.400 --> 00:12:22.730
>>THIS IS A TRAGEDY FOR
ONE MAN AND HIS PEOPLE.

00:12:22.730 --> 00:12:28.830


00:12:28.830 --> 00:12:32.100
AND THE EXPERTS WHO SAY
CLIMATE CHANGE IS A KEY FACTOR

00:12:32.100 --> 00:12:35.300
BEHIND THE PROBLEMS IN KENYA
BELIEVE IT COULD ALSO HIT

00:12:35.300 --> 00:12:38.630
FOOD PRODUCTION IN
MORE DEVELOPED COUNTRIES.

00:12:38.630 --> 00:12:41.870
WARM, DROUGHT-PRONE AREAS
OF AUSTRALIA, ARGENTINA,

00:12:41.870 --> 00:12:45.630
AND THE UNITED
STATES ARE AT RISK.

00:12:45.630 --> 00:12:48.430
AND THEY ARE ALL COUNTRIES
THAT EXPORT LARGE QUANTITIES

00:12:48.430 --> 00:12:51.300
OF FOOD ACROSS
THE GLOBE.

00:12:51.300 --> 00:12:53.670
HALF THE WORLD'S
POPULATION COULD FACE A

00:12:53.670 --> 00:12:58.370
CLIMATE-INDUCED FOOD CRISIS
BY THE END OF THE CENTURY.

00:12:58.370 --> 00:13:06.470


00:13:06.470 --> 00:13:11.470
IN MORE TEMPERATE CLIMATES THE
CONSEQUENCES OF CLIMATE CHANGE

00:13:11.470 --> 00:13:13.930
ARE UNLIKELY TO
BE SO EXTREME.

00:13:13.930 --> 00:13:16.700
BUT SOME FARMERS SAY THE
EFFECTS ON AGRICULTURE

00:13:16.700 --> 00:13:19.570
ARE ALREADY
CLEAR TO SEE.

00:13:19.570 --> 00:13:31.370


00:13:31.370 --> 00:13:34.070
THE LECKFORD ESTATE IN
ENGLAND IS A FARM OF ABOUT

00:13:34.070 --> 00:13:36.630
4,000 ACRES THAT IS
OWNED AND RUN BY THE

00:13:36.630 --> 00:13:40.070
BRITISH SUPERMARKET
CHAIN, WAITROSE.

00:13:40.070 --> 00:13:43.070
MORE THAN A THOUSAND
FRIESIAN CATTLE PRODUCE

00:13:43.070 --> 00:13:46.370
MORE THAN FIVE MILLION LITERS
OF MILK A YEAR, AND APPLES,

00:13:46.370 --> 00:13:52.300
PEARS, MUSHROOMS, AND
CEREALS ARE ALSO GROWN HERE.

00:13:52.300 --> 00:13:55.330
FARMER IAN DALTON SAYS
THAT GLOBAL WARMING

00:13:55.330 --> 00:13:58.970
IS ALREADY
HAVING AN EFFECT.

00:13:58.970 --> 00:14:03.570
DURING THE 2007, 2008 YEARS
AND THE HARVEST OF 2007,

00:14:03.570 --> 00:14:06.530
WE'VE SEEN
HUGE VOLATILITY.

00:14:06.530 --> 00:14:10.570
SO, YOU KNOW, PRICES OF WHEAT
DOUBLING AND THEN HALVING

00:14:10.570 --> 00:14:13.900
IN LESS THAN 12 MONTHS IS AN
EXTRAORDINARILY DIFFICULT

00:14:13.900 --> 00:14:18.370
POSITION FOR FARMERS TO
MANAGE THEIR BUSINESSES.

00:14:18.370 --> 00:14:21.300
>>IAN HAS SEEN THE PRICES HE
HAS PAID FOR A TON OF WHEAT

